design:
Mirror the Thetis check in RadioService.SetVfo:

```
if (ctun) {
    long proposedShift = CwOffset.EffectiveLoHz(currentMode, clamped) - radioLo;
    long ifCapacity = (long)(sampleRate * 0.46);  // Thetis uses sample_rate * 0.92 / 2
    retune = Math.Abs(proposedShift) > ifCapacity;
} else {
    retune = true;
}
```

When retune is true, treat as CTUN-off path: update VfoHz + RadioLoHz to clamped, call ActiveClient?.SetVfoAHz. When false, classic CTUN behaviour (dial only, panadapter frozen, WDSP shift handles the offset).

No changes needed to:
- DspPipelineService.OnRadioStateChanged ctunShiftHz computation — naturally becomes 0 when retune happened (RadioLoHz == VfoHz).
- DspPipelineService panadapter centre selection — works correctly with both branches.
- ConnectRetune path (RadioService.cs:481-485) — small-CTUN persistence stays valid; big jumps were already retuned so RadioLoHz == VfoHz.

Out of scope for this issue (Thetis has it, Zeus can add later): the second Thetis check — 'dial outside visible panadapter span' — needs access to display span from RadioService, which is more wiring. The IF-capacity check alone fixes the TCI band-change repro.
